<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>VCF Operations 9.0 on My Cloudy World</title><link>http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/categories/vcf-operations-9.0/</link><description>Recent content in VCF Operations 9.0 on My Cloudy World</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><managingEditor>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</managingEditor><webMaster>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</webMaster><copyright>Copyright © 2019–2025, Gary Blake; all rights reserved.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 10 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/categories/vcf-operations-9.0/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Using VMware.Sdk.Vcf.Ops: Commands for VCF Operations</title><link>http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-operations-cmdlets/</link><pubDate>Thu, 10 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</author><guid>http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-operations-cmdlets/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;VCF PowerCLI 9.0 now includes a module called &lt;code&gt;VMware.Sdk.Vcf.Ops&lt;/code&gt;, this modules contains auto-generated cmdlets to support VCF Operations Public APIs. Use can use this post as a quick reference guide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="connecting-to-a-vcf-operations-instance-with-local-credentials"&gt;Connecting to a VCF Operations Instance with Local Credentials&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start a PowerShell session.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect to a VCF Operations instance using local credentials by running the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;Connect-VcfOpsServer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;-Server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;flt-ops01a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;rainpole&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;io&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;-User&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;admin&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;-Password&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;VMw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;@re1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;VMw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;@re1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="3"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Once connected the following information is stored in &lt;code&gt;$defaultOpsConnections&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;ServiceUri : https://flt-ops01a.rainpole.io/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;SessionSecret : 54aa4efb-3acd-4a14-ad75-10e66742a96d::c38a1c14-0ea4-4f3f-abe8-40afc55bae6d
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;User : admin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;IsConnected : True
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;Id : /VcfOpsServer&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;admin@flt-ops01a.rainpole.io:443/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;Name : flt-ops01a.rainpole.io
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;Uid : /VcfOpsServer&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;admin@flt-ops01a.rainpole.io:443/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;ProductVersion : VCF Operations 9.0.0.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt; 9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;ServerUri : https://flt-ops01a.rainpole.io/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;UUID : /VcfOpsServer&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;admin@flt-ops01a.rainpole.io:443/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt;11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;Port : &lt;span class="m"&gt;443&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="4"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disconnect from a VCF Operations instance by running the following command:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="ln"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;Disconnect-VcfOpsServer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;-Server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;flt-ops01a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;rainpole&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="display-all-vcf-operations-get-command-details"&gt;Display All VCF Operations GET Command Details&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start a PowerShell session.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>